Just to answer your second query, yes you can implement `insertBefore` in a singly linked list using a pointer which points to the previous node in addition to the one pointing to the current node. Here&#39;s how it looks. Please note that error handling is omitted for simplicity&#39;s sake.

	

    public void insertBefore(T data1, T data2) {
    		Node p = null;
    		Node curr = headNode;
    		while (curr.data != data1) {
    			p = curr;
    			curr = curr.nextNode;
    		}
    
    		Node insertNode = new Node();
    		insertNode.data = data2;
    		p.nextNode = insertNode;
    		insertNode.nextNode = curr;
    		size = size + 1;
    	}

